org.primaresearch.collections

Interface IndexedMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key type
    V - Value type
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexedMapImpl

    public interface IndexedMap<K,V>
extends java.util.Map<K,V>
    Extended map interface that adds indexed access.

    Note: A common bug is using the get(key) method instead of the getAt(index) method for indexed access. Java implicitly converts int to Integer when calling get(Object key). Unfortunately there is no way to check if the passed key is of the type the type parameter specifies.

    clc
